 off.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526ff227e4b0ffc73763b658\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T17:38:32.962Z\">5.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Martin Lawrence says EDF<strong> hasn't made its mind up yet</strong> on whether it plans to raise prices.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526ff107e4b0ded76c0a910a\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T17:35:07.588Z\">5.35pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Ramsay Dunning of Co-operative Energy, says the energy sector has a perception problem. It looks like an oligopoly. He doesn't think it is, but argues that potential new market entrants are deterred by lack of market transparency.</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>I am not asking for the breakup of the big six, but we need to do something to change that appearance.</p> </blockquote> <p>He argues that power generation and retail supply of energy to households should be split. This &quot;vertical integration&quot; feeds the perception of an uncompetitive industry.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526ff088e4b0ded76c0a9109\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T17:31:48.534Z\">5.31pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Alan Whitehead, Labour, wants to know why 'big six' energy company price rises march in step. Ian Peters of British Gas says 2013 is an unusual year, partly because of the introduction of the eco-levy.&nbsp;</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fee97e4b01566f5a3943b\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T17:24:13.446Z\">5.24pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Neil Clitheroe of Scottish Power takes up the eco levy tax argument, saying the UK is one of the few countries that puts the charge on bills. &quot;If that separate people we could reference that point straight away and say that's what we pay.&quot;&nbsp;</p> <p><em>JR -This is emerging as the line-to-take for the energy companies today.</em></p> <p>Martin Lawrence of EDF chips in, asking for more stability and clarity about the future of the green levy.</p> </div> <p class=\"block-time updated-time\">Updated <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T17:24:44.907Z\">at 5.24pm GMT</time></p> </div> <div id=\"block-526fee0de4b0ffc73763b652\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T17:20:27.049Z\">5.20pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Now Ian Peters of British Gas argues that the eco levy should be shifted into general taxation, rather than put on customers' bills.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fed8ee4b0ffc73763b651\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T17:18:22.792Z\">5.18pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Christopher Pincher (Conservative), citing research from the Institute of Public Policy Research, says that 1/3 of British Gas price hike could be avoided if they delivered on energy efficiency. Peters says he doesn't understand where that analysis comes from.</p> </div> <p class=\"block-time updated-time\">Updated <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T17:18:35.693Z\">at 5.18pm GMT</time></p> </div> <div id=\"block-526fecc1e4b08c7e086ff14f\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T17:14:32.065Z\">5.14pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Ian Peters of British Gas says 1% of the fall in customers' energy use is not related to energy efficiency measures, suggesting this could be related to changing habits.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fec3ee4b01566f5a3943a\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time