er does the Co-Op benefit from economies of scale.&nbsp;</p> <p>And he adds:</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>We can sustain ourselves on lower levels of profitability</p> </blockquote> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fe8a3e4b08c7e086ff14c\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T16:57:51.627Z\">4.57pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Natalie Bennett, leader of the Green party, has given her reaction to today's committee meeting:</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>It's excellent that senior executives are 'facing the music' before MPs today, but what we need on energy policy&nbsp;is not uncomfortable squirms but effective action.</p> <p>&quot;MPs are right to ask why energy prices have gone up by 9% on&nbsp;average when wholesale gone up by 1.7% this year, but what we really need are answers as to how we can have affordable energy bills in future, warm comfortable homes and an energy industry that provides a range of jobs and economic opportunities for Britain.</p> <p>That means we need a serious focus on energy conservation, particularly home insulation, to end the scandal exposed today by the Children Society of the more than half of the 3 million children living in poverty who say their home is uncomfortably cold, and the 26% who say their home suffers from mould or damp.</p> </blockquote> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fe84ce4b01566f5a39439\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T16:55:08.948Z\">4.55pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>A quick recap for anyone just joining us: senior executives at nPower (RWE) and SSE have defended their price rise policy, claiming it was unavoidable because rises in the wholesale price of gas. E.ON refused to rule out a price rise. All three denied working in concert and insisted they ran transparent companies.</p> <p>Energy minnow Ovo Energy, which has 140,000 customers, pleaded for more competition and said it could cut customers' bills if it was in the position of RWE.</p> <p>A snap verdict: no MP has landed a killer blow, but they are clearly not buying the energy companies' arguments.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fe5f7e4b01566f5a39438\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T16:54:24.816Z\">4.54pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>The Thatcher room in Portcullis House, where energy bosses are meeting MPs, is still looking pretty empty.</p> <p>It seems appropriate this debate about energy prices - effectively a debate about the effectiveness of competition started by Margaret Thatcher - is happening here.&nbsp;</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fe28be4b01566f5a39436\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T16:30:40.303Z\">4.30pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>The division bell is ringing and members are off to vote. Should be back in 10 minutes, says the committee chair.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fe237e4b08c7e086ff14a\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T16:29:59.966Z\">4.29pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Ian Peters of British Gas defends the difference between his firm's 9.2% increase in wholesale costs, when Ofgem showed that wholesale prices were going up by much less. He says that this is comparing apples with bananas, because the Ofgem figures are forward-looking.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fe19ee4b01566f5a39435\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T16:28:00.726Z\">4.28pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Ramsay Dunning of Co-op Energy says his energy firm is run in a very different way from the big six.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fe13fe4b08c7e086ff149\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T16:25:55.677Z\">4.25pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Now up is Neil Clitheroe of Scottish Power, who is defending his company's 8.6% price rise. He says it is &quot;extremely difficult to make these decisions&quot; and tells Owen his bonus has been flat for the past few years.</p> <p>Owen &quot;You are comfortable taking bonuses when your customers are struggling?&quot;</p> <p>Clitheroe says he is not comfortable with what is happening to his customers.</p> </div> <p class=\"block-time updated-time\">Updated <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T16:27:14.881Z\">at 4.27pm GMT</time></p> </div> <div id=\"block-526fe0dfe4b0ffc73763b647\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T16:24:07.088Z\">4.24pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Peters says that Sam Laidlaw, Centrica boss, is getting a bonus because the company is making profits by expanding overseas.</p> <p>Owen: &quot;You don't lead by example. The rest of the country is struggling wage freezes.&quot;</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fe03de4b01566f5a39433\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T16:22:51.572Z\">4.22pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Ian Peters, managing director of British Gas, steps up for this question.</p> <p>He says executive remuneration is a bigger issue than just the energy issue and bonuses are set by an independent committee. &quot;It is very transparent and the terms are put to our remuneration committee every year.&quot;</p> <p>Owen sounds unimpressed by this argument. Since 2008 the average British Gas bill has gone up by 38%, while the chief executive of Centrica - who is not here today - had a rise of 36%, up to &pound;2.35m, he says. &quot;That is the question I am asking, how do you justify that?&quot;</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fdfb1e4b08c7e086ff147\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T16:19:32.091Z\">4.19pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>First up, Albert Owen (Lab): &quot;How can you justify when people are struggling and inflation is at 2-2.5%, how can you justify these rises and give your executives huge pay rises?</p> <p>&quot;Don't you think that the restraint that the British public is under should apply to your executives as well?&quot;</p> <p>Owen says he is a customer for British Gas, but he might not be for much longer.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fdf3fe4b01566f5a39431\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T16:16:52.277Z\">4.16pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>And on that note, the first session is wrapping up.. next up Scottish Power, British Gas, EDF and Co-op Energy.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fde3ce4b01566f5a39430\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T16:15:47.179Z\">4.15pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Fitzpatrick calls on his competitors &quot;to treat every customer fairly&quot;. He says if energy companies want to be trusted, you shouldn't be able to save 16% moving from one tariff from another, where profit margins are 5%.</p> <p>&quot;Everytime they call up to complain, they get a deal dangled in front of them.&quot;</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fddd5e4b01566f5a3942f\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T16:11:10.042Z\">4.11pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Now it is Guy Johnson's turn to defend nPower's transparency record. He concedes that customers should have&nbsp;&quot;fewer tariffs, clearer bills&quot;.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fdd0ae4b01566f5a3942e\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T16:08:08.071Z\">4.08pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>William Morris of SSE defends his company's record on transparency and says they plan to act on recommendations from accountancy firm BDO to make improvements. The energy and climate change committee called on the firms to act on this report in a report earlier this year.</p> <p>Read the background on transparency recommendations <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/business/2012/nov/21/ofgem-gas-price-fixing-warning\">here</a>.</p> </div> <p class=\"block-time updated-time\">Updated <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T16:09:33.139Z\">at 4.09pm GMT</time></p> </div> <div id=\"block-526fdc78e4b01566f5a3942d\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T16:06:31.496Z\">4.06pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Dan Byles, a Conservative MP, says he is none the wiser about energy companies' structure and profits. &quot;Would you accept that your accounting and reporting practices fail the basic tests of transparency?&quot;</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fdb6be4b01566f5a3942c\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T16:03:31.500Z\">4.03pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Tony Cocker is defending E.ON's profit margins and return on capital. In Germany, E.ON recently closed a gas-fired power station. Morris of SSE chips in and says they also have concerns about some of their gas-fired power stations in Germany.</p> <p>Phillip Lee says he is puzzled about why generation is not more profitable, when people cannot simply decide not to use gas and electricity. He adds&quot; If governments go down the energy efficiency route, it is going to screw your business isn't it?&quot;</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fdac9e4b0ffc73763b641\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T15:59:22.854Z\">3.59pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Fitzpatrick of Ovo Energy is picking up his theme of more competition. He says Ofgem have &quot;almost entirely failed in our lifetime.&quot; His firm is four years old. The latest energy market review does almost nothing to address the monopoly position that the big six enjoy.</p> <p>If all the energy companies charged the same prices as Ovo, there would be a &pound;3.7bn saving for consumers.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fd9b7e4b01566f5a3942b\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T15:54:47.265Z\">3.54pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Phillip Lee, a Conservative MP, wants to know how many of the firms employed public relations companies before coming in. &quot;There is a suspicion that you are a chorus line acting in concert.&quot;</p> </div> <p class=\"block-time updated-time\">Updated <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T15:56:19.826Z\">at 3.56pm GMT</time></p> </div> <div id=\"block-526fd907e4b01566f5a3942a\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T15:52:05.440Z\">3.52pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Ian Lavery, a Labour MP, is on the attack about fuel poverty and profits.</p> <p>&quot;How can these profits be fair when people cannot afford to pay for their energy?&quot;</p> <p>William Morris of SSE insists that the industry's profit margins are lower than the supermarkets, but adds &quot;I do accept the point it is still a big number.&quot;</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fd87de4b0ded76c0a9100\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T15:48:57.207Z\">3.48pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Tony Cocker of E.ON says he has written for to the prime minister calling for a competition inquiry.</p> <p>He says that he fundamentally believes the market is competitive, but acknowledges they are not trusted. &quot;It would be really helpful to de-politicise this debate, get experts to look at it and sort it out once and for all.&quot;</p> </div> <p class=\"block-time updated-time\">Updated <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T15:49:03.525Z\">at 3.49pm GMT</time></p> </div> <div id=\"block-526fd77ee4b01566f5a39429\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T15:46:47.374Z\">3.46pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>A question to Fitzpatrick of Ovo Energy: &quot;If I was to give you half of RWE's business could you do it better and make it cheaper?&quot;</p> <p>Fitzpatrick says he would be delighted to, saying that RWE /nPower is responsible for highest bills.</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>We are all trying to track were the money has gone and you will never find it. These companies are the best filibusters in the business.</p> <p>But he rejects Robertson's idea that the energy companies should have their generation arms hived off from retail. He argues the biggest problem is lack of competition. &quot;Effective competition is the only solution to lower bills.&quot;</p> </blockquote> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fd727e4b08c7e086ff145\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T15:41:36.350Z\">3.41pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Will you promise not to cut elderly and disabled people off in the winter even if they do not pay their bills, Robertson asks.</p> <p>The energy bosses are saying nobody gets cut off.</p> </div> <p class=\"block-time updated-time\">Updated <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T15:42:48.463Z\">at 3.42pm GMT</time></p> </div> <div id=\"block-526fd65de4b08c7e086ff143\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T15:41:09.802Z\">3.41pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Robertson is still unhappy about the lack of transparency over big six profits.</p> <p>&nbsp;According to Ofgem, energy companies make 23% profit on generating electricity while their own figures suggest profits 17-23%, he says. Yet these profits are not taken into account by their retail arms, when companies raise consumers' bills. Why?</p> <p>How can shareholders get dividends on 20% energy generation profits, while consumers get 10% increases in their energy bills he asks.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fd61be4b01566f5a39428\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T15:37:45.688Z\">3.37pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Guy Johnson of nPower says the firm has taken &pound;170m in subsidies for renewable energy in the last few years, &quot;vastly dwarfed by the &pound;2.3bn we have invested&quot;.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fd561e4b01566f5a39426\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T15:36:41.231Z\">3.36pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>John Robertson (Labour) wants to know where these companies are paying taxes.</p> <p>Tony Cocker of E.On replies:</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>I assume therefore that the German company pays German taxes and the British company pays British taxes.</p> </blockquote> <p>Robertson</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>I would expect a CEO to know...</p> </blockquote> <p>Cocker</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>We pay taxes here in the UK and we are proud to pay taxes in the UK...</p> </blockquote> <p>Robertson</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>You are not trying hard enough...</p> </blockquote> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fd4d3e4b08c7e086ff141\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T15:33:40.392Z\">3.33pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>John Robertson for Labour gets to the heart of the matter:</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>Do you understand that the people in this country do not trust you? How do you expect to get that trust back?</p> </blockquote> <p>William Morris (NPower) says 15 months ago he was one of those people. He is a newcomer to the energy industry.</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>We have a profound problem on our hands.</p> </blockquote> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fd3f2e4b08c7e086ff140\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T15:31:07.927Z\">3.31pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Albert Owen, Labour, is also asking about the eco levies, pointing out they were only introduced in April.</p> <p>&quot;Many of my constituents don't have the luxury of those discounts because they don't have a dual-fuel bill,&quot; he adds. So why should they have to pay more?</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fd348e4b0ffc73763b63c\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T15:27:20.537Z\">3.27pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>If the green levies are lifted will you pass on the saving to your customers, asks Pincher (Con) referring to David Cameron's pledge to roll back green levies.</p> <p>&quot;Unquestionably yes,&quot; says Johnson of nPower. &quot;Pound for pound, penny for penny, that should come straight off the customer's bill.&quot;</p> <p>Tony Cocker of E.ON is not giving a yes or no answer.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fd29de4b08c7e086ff13f\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T15:24:18.137Z\">3.24pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Christopher Pincher, a Conservative member of the committee, is asking nPower's Guy Johnson why their eco levy costs are higher than their competitors.</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>We will do absolutely everything in our interest to deliver them as efficiently as possible.</p> </blockquote> <p>Johnson says fuel poverty is profoundly worrying for him. &quot;We don't want anybody to be in that situation.&quot;</p> </div> <p class=\"block-time updated-time\">Updated <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T15:24:37.751Z\">at 3.24pm GMT</time></p> </div> <div id=\"block-526fd1d0e4b01566f5a39425\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T15:21:02.659Z\">3.21pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Back onto the eco levies, Guy Johnson of nPower says the scheme add up to &pound;60 on the bill.&nbsp;</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fd0d4e4b0ded76c0a90f9\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T15:17:25.392Z\">3.17pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Tony Cocker of E.ON, which has not yet raised its prices, says the firm has not yet decided if it will raise its prices. &quot;We will hold our prices as long as we can.&quot;</p> <p>This doesn't impress the committee - one MP says &quot;it means nothing &quot;.</p> <p>Cocker blames the green levies, describing them as &quot;a regressive poll tax&quot;.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fcfc1e4b0ded76c0a90f5\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T15:14:20.153Z\">3.14pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Barry Gardiner, a Labour member of the committee, is going after the companies on their price rises, and why despite different strategies they all put up their prices at the same time.</p> <p>William Morris of SSE counters &quot;things are changing&quot;. He says the firm has made a loss of &pound;21m.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fceb0e4b0ffc73763b637\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T15:06:54.642Z\">3.06pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Tony Cocker claims E.ON has invested &pound;7bn in the last five years. &quot;There is some misinformation that investment has stalled in the last five years, that isn't what I am hearing.&quot;</p> <p>He goes on to claim they have invested 100% of what they have earned in the last 5 years.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fce3ce4b0ffc73763b636\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T15:04:42.778Z\">3.04pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Stephen Fitzpatrick of Ovo Energy says in January 2012 they were the first energy company to announce a price cut. Although it is worth pointing out this cut was wiped out in the following April with a price rise of 5.8%...</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fcd7ee4b08c7e086ff13d\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T15:02:42.389Z\">3.02pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Guy Johnson of nPower is being quizzed about profits and whether UK profits are being fed back to the home company. nPower is owned by German utility RWE. He insists &quot;there is no old fashioned transfer pricing going on&quot;, but acknowledges&nbsp;&quot;an element of concern and suspicion.. that there are excess profits&quot;.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fcbe8e4b01566f5a39423\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T14:59:47.512Z\">2.59pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Tony Cocker of E.ON denies the charge that companies are subsidising their retail business.&nbsp;He says his business is very transparent.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fcb49e4b08c7e086ff13c\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T14:53:23.093Z\">2.53pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Stephen Fitzpatrick continues his attack on the big six: &quot;A significant number of the big six are charging the maximum they can get away with.&quot;</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fc9ffe4b08c7e086ff13a\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T14:50:24.986Z\">2.50pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Now up Stephen Fitzpatrick from energy minnow Ovo Energy, based in Bristol with 140,000 customers.</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>I cannot explain any of these prices rises. They are not the prices we see in the liquid wholesale market.</p> <p>Like some of the committee members I have been somewhat confused looking at the explanations for some of the price rises.</p> </blockquote> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fc89ee4b01566f5a39420\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T14:43:37.674Z\">2.43pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Morris of SSE is getting grilled over the breakdown of SSE's costs.</p> <p>The wholesale energy proportion of the bill is half the bill, another large proportion is transporting energy, the cost of social and environmental schemes account for 10% of bills and have gone up 13%.</p> <p>&quot;We would like to see those costs off customer bills and coming out of taxation.&quot; He says he is paying the same proportion of his income on these levies as someone living in fuel poverty, which &quot;clearly isn't morally defensible&quot;.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fc80de4b08c7e086ff139\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T14:38:24.815Z\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>William Morris of SSE says that OFGEM have revised their position and says company &quot;regrets profoundly&quot; having to put up prices. &quot;None of us want prices to rise.&quot;</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fc7c6e4b01566f5a3941f\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T14:36:36.220Z\">2.36pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>First question is on prices, how can they be explained when Ofgem says wholesale prices have only risen by 1.7%?</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fc79ae4b01566f5a3941e\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T14:35:39.110Z\">2.35pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>We are getting started... introductions from E.ON, SSE, NPower and Ovo Energy</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fc603e4b0ded76c0a90f3\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T14:31:31.116Z\">2.31pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Some background reading:</p> <p>The BBC has put together this handy <a href=\"http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-24670741?print=true\">explainer on the Big Six</a></p> <p>The Guardian's energy editor Terry Macalister&nbsp;has set out <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/business/2013/oct/27/questions-big-six-energy-firms-must-answer-prices\">5 questions they must </a><a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/business/2013/oct/27/questions-big-six-energy-firms-must-answer-prices\">answer</a>.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fc535e4b0ffc73763b633\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T14:27:55.328Z\">2.27pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Here is a full run down of the <a href=\"http://www.parliament.uk/business/committees/committees-a-z/commons-select/energy-and-climate-change-committee/news/energy-prices/\">agenda</a>. As my colleague Jill Treanor has pointed out, it's worth noting that <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/business/blog/2013/oct/28/energy-firms-mps-eon-chief-executive\">only E.ON have bothered to put up their UK chief executive</a>.</p> <p>Panel 1 at 2.30pm</p> <ul> <li> <p>Tony Cocker, Chief Executive Officer, E.ON</p> </li> <li> <p>William Morris, Managing Director, SSE</p> </li> <li> <p>Guy Johnson, External Affairs Director, RWEnpower</p> </li> <li> <p>Stephen Fitzpatrick, Managing Director, Ovo Energy</p> </li> </ul> <p>Panel 2 at 3.30pm</p> <ul> <li> <p>Neil Clitheroe, Chief Executive Officer - Retail and Generation, ScottishPower</p> </li> <li> <p>Ian Peters, Managing Director - Energy, British Gas</p> </li> <li> <p>Martin Lawrence, Managing Director - Energy Sourcing and Customer Supply, EDF Energy</p> </li> <li> <p>Ramsay Dunning, Group General Manager, Co-operative Energy</p> </li> </ul> <p>Panel 3 at 4.30pm</p> <ul> <li>Andrew Wright, Interim Chief Executive Officer, Ofgem</li> </ul> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fc467e4b08c7e086ff137\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T14:23:04.335Z\">2.23pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Interest in the select committee hearing seems to be huge.</p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/jessbrammar/statuses/395188069055598592\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Overheard in queue to watch select committee: &quot;oh, everyo