ery different way from the big six.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fe13fe4b08c7e086ff149\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T16:25:55.677Z\">4.25pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Now up is Neil Clitheroe of Scottish Power, who is defending his company's 8.6% price rise. He says it is &quot;extremely difficult to make these decisions&quot; and tells Owen his bonus has been flat for the past few years.</p> <p>Owen &quot;You are comfortable taking bonuses when your customers are struggling?&quot;</p> <p>Clitheroe says he is not comfortable with what is happening to his customers.</p> </div> <p class=\"block-time updated-time\">Updated <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T16:27:14.881Z\">at 4.27pm GMT</time></p> </div> <div id=\"block-526fe0dfe4b0ffc73763b647\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T16:24:07.088Z\">4.24pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Peters says that Sam Laidlaw, Centrica boss, is getting a bonus because the company is making profits by expanding overseas.</p> <p>Owen: &quot;You don't lead by example. The rest of the country is struggling wage freezes.&quot;</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-526fe03de4b01566f5a39433\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-29T16:22:51.572Z\">4.22pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Ian Peters, managing director of British Gas, steps up for this question.</p> <p>He says executive remuneration is a bigger issue than just the energy issue and bonuses are set by an independent committee. &quot;It is very transparent and the terms are put to our remuneration committee every year.&quot;</p> <p>Owen sounds unimpressed by this argument. Since 2008 the average British Gas bill has gone up by 38%, while the chief executive of Centrica - who is no